commit 51de48f1b464e5cceceb05aee5d07a1f56a2b44c
Author: Jack Rudenko <i@madappgang.com>
Date:   Sat Dec 13 18:02:27 2025 +1100

    fix: Windows spawn ENOENT - runtime platform detection
    
    The `isWindows` constant was evaluated at build time by Bun's bundler,
    causing it to be inlined as `false` when built on macOS. This meant
    Windows users got `spawn claude ENOENT` because `shell: true` wasn't
    being passed to spawn().
    
    Fix: Changed `isWindows` from a module-level constant to a function
    that evaluates `process.platform` at runtime, ensuring correct
    Windows detection regardless of build platform.
    
    Fixes: spawn claude ENOENT on Windows
    
    ðŸ¤– Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

Author: Jack Rudenko <i@madappgang.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 28 21:25:08 2025 +1100

    Initial commit: Claudish - OpenRouter proxy for Claude Code
    
    A proxy server that enables Claude Code to work with any OpenRouter model
    (Grok, GPT-5, Gemini, DeepSeek, etc.) with automatic message transformation.
    
    Features:
    - Model-specific adapters for Grok, Gemini, OpenAI, DeepSeek, Qwen, MiniMax
    - Interactive and single-shot CLI modes
    - MCP server support
    - Monitor mode for debugging
    - Comprehensive test suite

    fix: Windows spawn ENOENT - runtime platform detection
    
    The `isWindows` constant was evaluated at build time by Bun's bundler,
    causing it to be inlined as `false` when built on macOS. This meant
    Windows users got `spawn claude ENOENT` because `shell: true` wasn't
    being passed to spawn().
    
    Fix: Changed `isWindows` from a module-level constant to a function
    that evaluates `process.platform` at runtime, ensuring correct
    Windows detection regardless of build platform.
